g average 14.5/29k burns.<br>
<br>
Let me show you how incredibly overpowered that is. On an average raid my guild will have anywhere from 4-8 wizards present. We'll say 5 is the average. With very few exceptions, most fights I'll end up with around 80% mana left over. This basically means that when a mob gets down to around 80khp we could nuke him dead with 5 wizards (5 x 13.5k average x 20% crits). With a little luck, 5 raid guild wizards could potentially dish out 140k damage in 6 seconds. Sure it wouldn't happen often, but it is not unreasonable to say that 5 wizards could easily average 100k on a team burn.<br>
<br>
Not like it matters much anyway. The mobs that people where whining about being perma-dead to Team MB can all be nuked down with SoS (except VS) anyway. Just this week a group of 5 (cleric was #6 but he went AFK) of us took down Wuoshi with 2 wizards and no healers. He went down like a cheerleader on prom night.<br>
<br>
I think SOE knew that MB in its original form would have trivialized all but the biggest HP mobs in the game. Even then, being able to do 10% in 6 seconds of even a 1 million HP mob is a bit overpowered.<br>
<br>
MB still has its uses, it's actually easy to use since you can hit the cap without being FM. <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
